clinicalDescription: Overview: A queasy sensation including an urge to vomit. Many causes of nausea. Presentation: Uncomfortable feeling in the chest, upper abdomen, or back of the throat; feeling sick to one's stomach Assessment: Self-report. Nausea can be a precursor to vomiting. Plan: Depends on the cause. Resting, eating bland foods, and avoiding strong stimuli to reduce nausea. OTC motion sickness medication may also help. Hydration. Prognosis: Usually acute and short-lived, but can be prolonged. If experience nausea in combination with other symptoms that may require medical attention.
